I've taken care of my skin probably since I was 18 and I use sun cream 60 SPF every time I'm outside.  I'm from Australia originally and Australian sun is really damaging to the skin.  Trust me using sun cream is a must to stop aging your skin.  I'm 70 now and I have virtually no wrinkles on my face at all and I look a lot younger, it all comes down to good genes, but a big part of it is staying out of strong sunshine & using sunscreen.
